My biggest insecurity used to be how skinny I was…

Here’s 5 things that helped me overcome feeling like a skinny bish 🙃

1. Real Food> Mass Gainers. Sure if you are on a time crunch calories are calories but I promise you’ll look and feel better eating Whole Foods.🍔

2. The best workout split is the one you can stay consistent with, for me it was a push, pull, legs, rest, repeat💪🏽

3. Track your food and workouts. What’s tracked is what will improve. How do you know you’re eating enough if you’re not tracking, how do you know you’re pushing yourself harder if you don’t remember what you did last workout 📝

4. Rest & Recovery: sleeping 7-8 hours a night is going to allow your body to rebuild the muscles that you broke down during your working and stretching/foam rolling will help alleviate any muscle soreness you have 😴

5. Hire a coach to hold you accountable, this was the biggest thing for me because I wouldn’t want to disappoint/ waste my coaches time during our weekly check ins 🔥

Hopefully these help and if you have any questions or interested in a custom coaching program dm me or comment below 💪🏽

Rotating running shoes have several benefits

1. Injury Prevention: By rotating between different pairs of shoes, runners can reduce the repetitive stress on the same muscles and joints, potentially lowering the risk of overuse injuries. Each shoe may provide slightly different support and cushioning, which helps distribute impact forces more evenly.

2. Extended Shoe Lifespan: Regularly rotating between multiple pairs of running shoes allows each pair to have more time to recover between runs. As a result, the cushioning and structure of the shoes tend to last longer, maximizing their overall lifespan.

3. Enhanced Performance: Different shoes cater to various types of running and terrain. Rotating shoes can provide runners with the advantages of different designs, such as stability, lightweight, or extra cushioning, depending on the specific needs of their workouts or races, potentially leading to improved performance.

It’s essential to choose shoes that are best for your running style and have similar characteristics to avoid abrupt changes in support or cushioning. You can always go to @charlotterunningcompany or @fleetfeetcharlotte for shoe recommendations best for you!
